[Clerk; MK]
cases #14CF7, #14CM7 called at 1:01pm. 
Defendant William C Rennhack in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights given; plea of " No Contest " entered in Case #14CF7 and in Case #14CM7; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified (ADA Shock submits victim impact statements); the Court accepts the pleas, finds Mr. Rennhack guilty in each case, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.


In Case #14CF7, the Court sentences Mr. Rennhack to 4 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 2 years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 2 years, consecutive to any other sentences in being.  
The Court finds that Mr. Rennhack is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that Mr. Rennhack is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served.

In Case #14CM7, the Court sentences Mr. Rennhack to serve 9 months Jail (to be served in the WSPS), consecutive to the sentence imposed in Case #14CF7, and consecutive to any other sentence in being.
The Court gives  0 days credit for time already served. 

On both cases, the Court STAYS the sentences and places Mr. Rennhack on Probation for 3 years in Case #14CF7 and for 1 year in Case #14CM7, with conditions (in case #14CF7, these conditions will become conditions of Extended Supervision if Probation is revoked): 

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with all recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--not to possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to take all prescribed medications as prescribed
--not to possess or consume alcohol 
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--not to engage in any acts or threats of violence
--no direct or indirect contact with Justin Frohmader, Jenna Frohmader or John Elvin
--to obtain/maintain fulltime employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision
--to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge in Case #14CF7
--to pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge in Case #14CM7
--to pay restitution of $1600 to Justin and Jenna Frohmader
--to pay resitution of $335 to Brad Stewart of American Pawn & Trading LLC 
--to pay the 10% restitution processing fee 

The Court will not allow expungement of these cases. 
Felony firearm/voting prohibition warnings are given.
Contact prohibition warnings/penalties given.
